ed1032SysBootDate.name: ed1032SysBootDate
ed1032SysBootDate.description: The date and time of the last IPL

ed1032SysFirmwareVersion.name: ed1032SysFirmwareVersion
ed1032SysFirmwareVersion.description: The current version of the firmware.

ed1032SysTypeNum.name: ed1032SysTypeNum
ed1032SysTypeNum.description: This object identifies ASCII type number for the unit.

ed1032SysModelNum.name: ed1032SysModelNum
ed1032SysModelNum.description: This object identifies ASCII model number for the unit.

ed1032SysMfg.name: ed1032SysMfg
ed1032SysMfg.description: This object identifies ASCII manufacturer for the unit.

ed1032SysPlantOfMfg.name: ed1032SysPlantOfMfg
ed1032SysPlantOfMfg.description: This object identifies ASCII plant of manufacturer for the unit.

ed1032SysSeqNum.name: ed1032SysSeqNum
ed1032SysSeqNum.description: This object identifies ASCII sequence number for the unit.

ed1032SysEcLevel.name: ed1032SysEcLevel
ed1032SysEcLevel.description: This object identifies ASCII EC level ID for the unit.

ed1032SysOemSerialNum.name: ed1032SysOemSerialNum
ed1032SysOemSerialNum.description: This object identifies ASCII OEM serial number for the unit.

ed1032SysOperStatus.name: ed1032SysOperStatus
ed1032SysOperStatus.description: The current operational status of the switch. The values are defined as follow: operational (1), redundant-failure (2), minor-failure (3), major-failure (4), not-operational (5).

ed1032SysState.name: ed1032SysState
ed1032SysState.description: If the edOperStatus of the switch is operational, the switch will be in one of the four states: online(1), coming-online(2), offline(3), and going-offline(4).

ed1032SysAdmStatus.name: ed1032SysAdmStatus
ed1032SysAdmStatus.description: The desired administrative status of the switch. A management station may place the switch in a desired state by setting this object accordingly. The desired administrative status are online(1) and offline(2). The online means setting the switch to be accessible by an external Fibre Channel port, and offline means setting the switch to be inaccessible.

ed1032FruTable.name: ed1032FruTable
ed1032FruTable.description: A table that contains one entry for each module.

ed1032FruEntry.name: ed1032FruEntry
ed1032FruEntry.description: An entry containing the service parameters of the module.

ed1032FruCode.name: ed1032FruCode
ed1032FruCode.description: Field Replaceable Unit. A hardware component of the product that is replaceable as an entire unit. Each module defined in this MIB has a fixed FRU code. The values are defined as follow: fru-none (0) , fru-bkplane (1), fru-ctp (2), fru-mpc (3), fru-cmm (4), fru-fan (5), fru-power (6), fru-panel (7), fru-gsm (8), fru-gls (9), fru-glx (10), fru-lsm (11), fru-gxx (12).

ed1032FruPosition.name: ed1032FruPosition
ed1032FruPosition.description: This object identifies the position of the module. Port cards start from 1 to 8. All other cards start from 1 to 1 or 2.

ed1032FruStatus.name: ed1032FruStatus
ed1032FruStatus.description: This object identifies the operational status of the module. The active(1) state indicates that the current module is active. The backup(2) state indicates that the back up module is used. update-busy (3) state indicates that the module is in the updating process. The failed(4) state indicates that the current module is failed.

ed1032FruPartNumber.name: ed1032FruPartNumber
ed1032FruPartNumber.description: This object identifies the part number of the module.

ed1032FruSerialNumber.name: ed1032FruSerialNumber
ed1032FruSerialNumber.description: This object identifies the serial number of the module.

ed1032FruPowerOnHours.name: ed1032FruPowerOnHours
ed1032FruPowerOnHours.description: This object indicates the number of the hours that the FRU has been in operation.

ed1032FruTestDate.name: ed1032FruTestDate
ed1032FruTestDate.description: This object indicates final test date of the module.

ed1032PortTable.name: ed1032PortTable
ed1032PortTable.description: A table that contains one entry for each switch port (stitch only).

ed1032PortEntry.name: ed1032PortEntry
ed1032PortEntry.description: An entry containing the information of the switch port.

ed1032PortIndex.name: ed1032PortIndex
ed1032PortIndex.description: This object identifies the switch port.

ed1032PortPhyState.name: ed1032PortPhyState
ed1032PortPhyState.description: This object identifies the physical state of the port.

ed1032PortOpStatus.name: ed1032PortOpStatus
ed1032PortOpStatus.description: This object identifies the operational status of the port. The online state indicates that user frames can be passed.

ed1032PortAdmStatus.name: ed1032PortAdmStatus
ed1032PortAdmStatus.description: The desired state of the port. A management station may place the port in a desired state by setting this object accordingly. The testing(3) state indicates that no user frames can be passed. As the result of either explicit management action or per configuration information accessible by the switch, ed1032PortAdmStatus is then changed to either the online(1) or testing(3) states, or remains in the offline state.

ed1032PortTxWords.name: ed1032PortTxWords
ed1032PortTxWords.description: This object counts the number of Fibre Channel words that the port has transmitted.

ed1032PortRxWords.name: ed1032PortRxWords
ed1032PortRxWords.description: This object counts the number of Fibre Channel words that the port has received.

ed1032PortTxFrames.name: ed1032PortTxFrames
ed1032PortTxFrames.description: This object counts the number of (Fibre Channel) frames that the port has transmitted.

ed1032PortRxFrames.name: ed1032PortRxFrames
ed1032PortRxFrames.description: This object counts the number of (Fibre Channel) frames that the port has received.

ed1032PortRxC2Frames.name: ed1032PortRxC2Frames
ed1032PortRxC2Frames.description: This object counts the number of Class 2 frames that the port has received.

ed1032PortRxC3Frames.name: ed1032PortRxC3Frames
ed1032PortRxC3Frames.description: This object counts the number of Class 3 frames that the port has received.

ed1032PortRxLCs.name: ed1032PortRxLCs
ed1032PortRxLCs.description: This object counts the number of Link Control frames that the port has received.

ed1032PortRxMcasts.name: ed1032PortRxMcasts
ed1032PortRxMcasts.description: This object counts the number of Multicast frames that the port has received.

ed1032PortTooManyRdys.name: ed1032PortTooManyRdys
ed1032PortTooManyRdys.description: This object counts the number of times when RDYs exceeds the frames received.

ed1032PortNoTxCredits.name: ed1032PortNoTxCredits
ed1032PortNoTxCredits.description: This object counts the amount of time that frame transmission is blocked by a transmit credit of zero. This is sampled once every 120 53.125 MHZ clocks, and the counter is incremented by 1 if the condition is true.

ed1032PortRxEncFrs.name: ed1032PortRxEncFrs
ed1032PortRxEncFrs.description: This object counts the number of encoding error or disparity error inside or outside frames received.

ed1032PortRxCrcs.name: ed1032PortRxCrcs
ed1032PortRxCrcs.description: This object counts the number of CRC errors detected for frames received.

ed1032PortRxTruncs.name: ed1032PortRxTruncs
ed1032PortRxTruncs.description: This object counts the number of truncated frames that the port has received.

ed1032PortRxTooLongs.name: ed1032PortRxTooLongs
ed1032PortRxTooLongs.description: This object counts the number of received frames that are too long.

ed1032PortRxBadEofs.name: ed1032PortRxBadEofs
ed1032PortRxBadEofs.description: This object counts the number of received frames that have bad EOF delimiter.

ed1032PortRxBadOs.name: ed1032PortRxBadOs
ed1032PortRxBadOs.description: This object counts the number of invalid Ordered Sets received.

ed1032PortC3Discards.name: ed1032PortC3Discards
ed1032PortC3Discards.description: This object counts the number of Class 3 frames that the port has discarded.

ed1032PortMcastTimedOuts.name: ed1032PortMcastTimedOuts
ed1032PortMcastTimedOuts.description: This object counts the number of Multicast frames that has been timed out.

ed1032PortTxMcasts.name: ed1032PortTxMcasts
ed1032PortTxMcasts.description: This object counts the number of Multicast frames that has been transmitted.

ed1032PortTxThroughput.name: ed1032PortTxThroughput
ed1032PortTxThroughput.description: This object presents the Bps transmission rate.

ed1032PortRxThroughput.name: ed1032PortRxThroughput
ed1032PortRxThroughput.description: This object presents the Bps reception rate.

ed1032PortScn.name: ed1032PortScn
ed1032PortScn.description: An ed1032PortScn(1) is generated whenever a Fc_Port changes its operational state. For instance, the Fc_Port goes from on-line to offline.

ed1032FruScn.name: ed1032FruScn
ed1032FruScn.description: An ed1032FruScn(2) is generated whenever a FRU status changes its operational state.
